WEBVTT

00:04.226 --> 00:05.087
Welcome to Life Church.

00:05.488 --> 00:07.831
We're here to help you become who God created you to be.

00:08.011 --> 00:09.073
And we'd love to hear from you.

00:09.113 --> 00:15.622
Take a quick survey at life.church slash podcast connect to let us know how we can support you on your faith journey.

00:15.983 --> 00:17.305
And now let's go to the message.

00:22.272 --> 00:32.466
Well, unfortunately, I know that there are a lot of you right now that are in the middle of real pain and you're hurting deeply and there's no doubt about it.

00:32.802 --> 00:37.188
when you're hurting deeply, that is very, very, very hard.

00:38.569 --> 00:44.237
But there's another kind of hard that we don't talk about often in the church.

00:45.078 --> 00:56.092
And that's the hard season when you're functioning and you're showing up and you're doing all the right things, but inside something still feels off.

00:57.474 --> 01:00.818
It's not that you're falling apart completely

01:01.666 --> 01:04.750
but you're still living consistently discouraged.

01:05.952 --> 01:14.323
It's not that you're battling with ongoing depression, but you're also not really happy and thriving.

01:15.444 --> 01:20.891
You're not in the middle of a crisis right now, but you still don't feel at peace.

01:22.213 --> 01:25.597
That place is what I call the middle.

01:26.619 --> 01:29.202
You're not in a horrible place

01:29.346 --> 01:31.630
where life is falling apart and you feel like you're about to break down.

01:32.271 --> 01:38.741
But you're also not experiencing the breakthrough and the joy of the Lord in the way that you know you should.

01:38.782 --> 01:42.428
That's the place that we call the middle.

01:43.589 --> 01:47.917
Not a horrible place, but it's definitely not where you want to be.

01:49.259 --> 01:56.050
And when you're stuck in the middle, you actually start to ask different types of questions.

01:56.962 --> 01:58.865
You're not asking like, God, are you there?

01:58.945 --> 01:59.786
Do you exist?

01:59.866 --> 02:03.472
But you're asking God, why don't I feel you right now?

02:04.894 --> 02:07.398
You're not asking, am I even saved?

02:07.418 --> 02:15.050
You're asking God, why am I still struggling with the same thing I've been carrying for so long?

02:16.272 --> 02:23.844
And for some reason, we don't talk about that place a lot in the church.

02:23.864 --> 02:25.426
We talk to the extremes.

02:25.794 --> 02:30.360
We talk to the times when you're down and you're out and you're hurting and you're desperate.

02:31.100 --> 02:36.647
And we talk about the breakthrough, the miracles, the power of God.

02:37.548 --> 02:41.733
We're good at talking directly about the hard times.

02:42.775 --> 02:45.418
God is close to the broken heart.

02:46.339 --> 02:48.622
He sees you in your pain.

02:49.222 --> 02:52.146
When you draw near to Him, He draws near to you.

02:52.290 --> 02:56.135
You cast all your anxiety on Him because He cares for you.

02:57.617 --> 03:06.149
And we're really good on the breakthrough God can do all things for Christ who gives you strength.

03:06.169 --> 03:10.135
You're an overcomer by the blood of the Lamb and by the words of your testimony.

03:10.335 --> 03:15.843
Your blessed coming in, no weapon formed against you will prosper in a moment God could heal you.

03:17.485 --> 03:21.170
We're good at speaking to the difficult times.

03:23.202 --> 03:24.644
It's a longer walk than I realize.

03:26.085 --> 03:29.750
And we're good at celebrating the breakthrough times.

03:31.893 --> 03:35.757
But what about when you're not falling apart?

03:38.020 --> 03:40.183
And you're not fully restored either.

03:43.386 --> 03:45.449
Where is God when you're stuck in the middle?

03:47.391 --> 03:52.978
If you've been there, or maybe you're there right now, not horrible,

03:53.826 --> 03:54.587
not great.

03:56.008 --> 04:00.333
I want to tell you that you are not alone, that God is with you.

04:01.494 --> 04:10.923
And I want to promise you, our good God is still at work, even when you feel stuck in the middle.

04:12.865 --> 04:21.714
So today, would you pray with me, Father, we need you in the desperate times.

04:22.786 --> 04:24.528
We need you in the breakthrough times.

04:25.610 --> 04:28.574
And God, we need you in the ordinary days when we're stuck in the middle.

04:29.756 --> 04:31.178
We thank you that you're always good.

04:31.218 --> 04:33.702
Your word is always true.

04:34.703 --> 04:35.945
You're always faithful.

04:36.906 --> 04:41.733
And so today God would cry out to you and ask you to meet us right where we are.

04:42.715 --> 04:47.461
That we could experience your goodness, your grace, your power, your love, your mercy, your healing and your hope.

04:47.481 --> 04:48.783
We pray this in Jesus' name.

04:49.224 --> 04:50.706
And everybody who agrees said,

04:51.202 --> 04:51.823
Amen.

04:51.863 --> 04:57.828
Elbow the person next to you and tell him if you're in the middle, God's not finished with you yet.

04:57.848 --> 04:59.410
Tell the other person the one you didn't choose.

04:59.430 --> 05:01.252
Tell him, hey, he's not finished with you either.

05:02.072 --> 05:03.674
He's not finished with you either.

05:03.714 --> 05:05.396
Tell your second choice.

05:06.817 --> 05:09.620
We are in a message series called Heal Your Hurting Mind.

05:09.700 --> 05:11.802
It's based on a new book that we released last week.

05:11.822 --> 05:14.705
The good news is it is it's helping people.

05:14.745 --> 05:18.468
The bad news is it was sold out most places most of the week.

05:18.909 --> 05:20.370
And so if you're

05:21.058 --> 05:32.209
If you're looking for one, it may take a little while to get to you there on back order and they're fulfilling back orders, but there will be books available and more importantly, we pray that there'll be healing available.

05:32.809 --> 05:35.712
The story behind the book, I wrote this with Dr. Wayne Chappelle.

05:35.732 --> 05:47.464
What I wanted to do is I wanted to write from a spiritual pastoral perspective, but it would be unwise and incomplete for me to do a book on mental health without a professional.

05:47.604 --> 05:49.746
And so I chose a very godly

05:50.050 --> 05:55.861
a very unique psychologist to write from the psychological and physiological side.

05:56.382 --> 06:01.712
And I want to review where we started last week because this isn't really like even just a four week message series.

06:02.053 --> 06:05.860
This is kind of like a four part message that we're building on week by week.

06:05.941 --> 06:12.914
Last week, we looked at the reality that in order to understand where you are, you have to know how God created you.

06:13.250 --> 06:15.092
God is a triune being.

06:15.132 --> 06:17.274
He created us in his image.

06:17.314 --> 06:19.196
He's father, son, and holy spirit.

06:19.476 --> 06:23.440
God created us as spirit, soul, and body.

06:24.041 --> 06:25.482
God cares about all of you.

06:25.562 --> 06:31.368
In other words, you are not just a body and you're not just a body with a soul.

06:31.448 --> 06:32.068
What is the soul?

06:32.128 --> 06:35.412
The soul is your mind, your will, and emotions.

06:35.432 --> 06:37.774
But you have to understand how God designed you.

06:37.814 --> 06:38.355
What are you?

06:38.735 --> 06:41.938
You are a spirit with a soul.

06:42.210 --> 06:43.632
that lives in a body.

06:44.333 --> 06:50.882
Primarily, you are a spiritual being that has a soul that lives in a physical body.

06:50.963 --> 07:01.778
And that's why when you call on Jesus, those of you who've been spiritually born anew, you are saved, I should say it over here, in a moment,

07:01.954 --> 07:04.577
It's the breakthrough, it's the salvation.

07:04.877 --> 07:10.544
The old is now gone, the new has come spiritually, you're made new in Christ, your sins are forgiven.

07:10.724 --> 07:14.448
You are a new creation, and that happens in a moment.

07:15.189 --> 07:24.019
We learned last week that salvation is instant, but sanctification, becoming like Jesus is a process.

07:24.720 --> 07:29.906
Salvation happens in a moment, but healing of the soul takes time.

07:30.274 --> 07:39.386
You can be saved instantly when you call on Jesus, but your mind, your will, and your emotions, they're renewed over time.

07:40.287 --> 07:51.421
So today, we're gonna look at a story in the Gospels, and we're gonna see a moment with Jesus where healing is actually not instant.

07:52.262 --> 07:58.610
In this story, sometimes healing is instant, but in this story, we're gonna see that healing is progressive,

07:59.010 --> 08:01.374
And it actually comes in stages.

08:02.175 --> 08:04.539
We're in Mark's gospel today, chapter eight.

08:05.080 --> 08:06.101
I'll start in verse 22.

08:07.063 --> 08:20.424
This is the word of God that says, they came to Bethsaida and some people, some people, we're gonna come back to that, brought a blind man and begged Jesus to touch him.

08:21.466 --> 08:26.674
He took the blind man by the hand and let him outside the village.

08:27.330 --> 08:36.043
When he had sped on the man's eyes and pulled his hand, put his hands on him, Jesus asked him, do you see anything?

08:36.924 --> 08:41.451
And the man looked up and said, I see people and they looked like trees walking around.

08:42.853 --> 08:45.557
Once more, everybody say once more.

08:46.839 --> 08:50.164
Once more, Jesus put his hands on the man's eyes.

08:51.065 --> 08:56.914
Then his eyes were opened, his sight was restored and he saw

08:57.154 --> 08:59.397
everything clearly.

09:00.758 --> 09:12.393
If you are a student of the Bible, you may say, I thought that Jesus put mud on a guy's eyes and then had him wash and he was healed with one touch.

09:13.294 --> 09:14.776
If you think that, you're actually right.

09:14.796 --> 09:20.803
There's another story in John's Gospel, John chapter nine, about a guy that was blind and Jesus spilled in the ground and put some mud on him.

09:21.263 --> 09:25.369
Jesus touched him one time when the guy washed it off, his eyes were healed.

09:25.389 --> 09:26.610
So in one story,

09:26.722 --> 09:28.144
He's healed with one touch.

09:28.785 --> 09:32.291
In this story, it actually takes two.

09:33.212 --> 09:35.916
Same savior, different process.

09:36.858 --> 09:37.839
Let's dive into the word.

09:37.859 --> 09:39.722
We're gonna look at verse 22 that tells us this.

09:40.343 --> 09:44.870
They came to Bessetta and some people, it's interesting.

09:44.890 --> 09:48.235
This is the second time we've seen that phrase in Mark's Gospel.

09:48.616 --> 09:55.186
Some people brought a blind man and begged Jesus to touch him.

09:55.522 --> 09:56.883
the phrase, some people.

09:57.004 --> 09:59.626
Some people brought a blind man to Jesus.

10:00.207 --> 10:07.255
A couple of weeks ago, we talked about another story in Mars Gospel where it said some people brought a man who couldn't walk to Jesus.

10:08.055 --> 10:10.678
Some people brought someone in need.

10:10.778 --> 10:13.401
The last time they couldn't get into Jesus because of the crowd.

10:13.621 --> 10:15.984
So they dug a hole to the roof and dropped their friend down.

10:16.004 --> 10:17.826
This time they just bring someone to Jesus.

10:17.866 --> 10:20.929
And what's interesting is that Mark doesn't tell us who some people are.

10:22.111 --> 10:25.394
There's no names, there's no background, there's no details because

10:25.506 --> 10:28.230
The point isn't who they are, but what they do.

10:29.551 --> 10:33.957
They don't need names because I think Mark perhaps was trying to show us that this could be anybody.

10:34.017 --> 10:39.004
It's ordinary, everyday people, just like you and just like me.

10:39.565 --> 10:50.900
Just some people that are not even named that have the faith to bring their friend to Jesus and God used ordinary people to start a miracle the blind man couldn't start on his own.

10:52.061 --> 10:52.722
Notice

10:52.962 --> 10:55.946
what these some people, these friends did and did not do.

10:56.987 --> 11:00.872
Notice they did not try to fix the blind man themselves.

11:01.793 --> 11:03.214
They didn't try to be the savior.

11:03.274 --> 11:05.517
They didn't need to have all the answers.

11:05.938 --> 11:08.501
They didn't try to heal him themselves.

11:09.222 --> 11:11.284
They didn't pretend they knew the solution.

11:12.005 --> 11:14.528
They just got their friend to Jesus.

11:15.669 --> 11:22.738
And Mark's gospel, when you look at how often he shows us that some people brought and some people brought,

11:22.818 --> 11:29.526
The gospel shows us clearly just how much we need each other.

11:31.107 --> 11:41.319
Because there are moments, and many of you are in one right now, moments you were never designed to do alone.

11:41.379 --> 11:51.410
Because one of the enemies, all this tactics is to isolate you, to take you away from support.

11:51.810 --> 11:57.758
to take you out of the body of Christ, because if he can disconnect you, he can discourage you.

11:58.159 --> 12:01.724
And when you're isolated, that's when the lives are the loudest.

12:04.107 --> 12:07.511
And that's one of the reasons why some of you are hurting right now.

12:09.074 --> 12:11.517
Well, I don't need people, and I don't need to open up to people.

12:11.998 --> 12:16.664
There's some of you watching online that like, I don't need the church, I'm just gonna consume content.

12:17.485 --> 12:21.170
And I'm not saying that's not bad, that's good, but it has all you have without

12:21.410 --> 12:26.536
the family of God, you're missing something that God wants to give you.

12:26.556 --> 12:27.958
And that's why we talk about it all the time.

12:27.998 --> 12:35.006
If you don't have strong Christian community, how do you fight off the attacks of the evil one?

12:35.026 --> 12:36.147
Because I can't do it by myself.

12:36.988 --> 12:38.470
I need the prayers of God's people.

12:38.750 --> 12:40.272
I need the encouragement of God's people.

12:40.532 --> 12:42.174
I need the correction of God's people.

12:42.414 --> 12:43.896
I need the support of God's people.

12:44.217 --> 12:47.060
I cannot do it without him and his people.

12:47.120 --> 12:48.882
And neither can you.

12:50.882 --> 12:56.508
Because if the devil can keep you disconnected, he can keep you stuck in your sickness.

12:57.349 --> 13:03.976
And this was me, I told you last week that I had a period where I just broke down.

13:04.977 --> 13:07.720
And for years and years and years, I was strong.

13:07.740 --> 13:20.754
Never thought it would happen to me, but the accumulation and the weight of the added work year after year, year after year, year after year, year after year, decade after decade caught up to me and it hit me pretty hard.

13:21.442 --> 13:44.939
And I don't know, I mean, if I'm looking at it objectively, it was probably fear of being vulnerable, and it's probably pride of not wanting people to know their pastor was struggling, but maybe it's fear, maybe it's a pride, but I just, I didn't wanna ask for help, and honestly, I didn't even know how to ask for help, because I'm the pastor, right?

13:45.219 --> 13:49.586
I'm the one who's not supposed to struggle, I'm the one who's supposed to help other people.

13:50.178 --> 13:52.461
And so I just hurt very privately for a while.

13:52.521 --> 13:54.804
And I would smile when I was preaching and preach with great passion.

13:55.265 --> 14:00.452
And I just continue to try unsuccessfully to fight the battle alone.

14:01.673 --> 14:02.655
Well, thank God for Amy.

14:02.695 --> 14:03.816
Every day I thank God for Amy.

14:04.036 --> 14:04.617
I thank God for Amy.

14:04.637 --> 14:05.679
I got the Holy Spirit and Amy.

14:05.699 --> 14:07.461
And sometimes I think they're the same person.

14:09.323 --> 14:15.451
And she reached out to a couple of people I worked with and a couple of good friends and said, we got to get Craig help.

14:15.492 --> 14:17.394
And so they did.

14:17.794 --> 14:19.577
Very godly man, Dr. Chappelle.

14:19.697 --> 14:29.493
I call him Dr. C, because it's much more fun to call him Dr. C. And the first thing he did after putting me through these tests is he assembled what he called my wingmen.

14:30.474 --> 14:32.397
And these are very close friends.

14:32.457 --> 14:33.439
These are trusted people.

14:33.499 --> 14:35.242
A couple of them were actually girls.

14:35.642 --> 14:37.666
And so it should have been my wingmen and my wingwomen.

14:38.507 --> 14:39.669
He assembled my wing people.

14:41.151 --> 14:43.014
Because, you know, I got to be politically correct.

14:43.234 --> 14:44.116
Or you'll come after me.

14:44.256 --> 14:45.458
Someone will take me out.

14:45.602 --> 14:48.066
I have my wing people, my wing people, I'm a tribe, my team.

14:48.387 --> 14:57.943
I have my support people to some people to help bring me closer to Jesus.

14:59.045 --> 15:05.836
Because I actually was saved instantly years ago when I knelt down in a softball field and called in the name of Jesus.

15:06.177 --> 15:09.362
I was saved instantly, but healing takes time.

15:10.530 --> 15:16.720
And I don't talk about it a lot because it's painful, but as you know, mental health is not static.

15:16.740 --> 15:21.067
It moves and it shifts and you often heal in stages.

15:22.008 --> 15:27.817
And part of my story is that I am the oldest adult child of an alcoholic.

15:28.398 --> 15:38.514
My dad, who, there was not a night after 10 o'clock in my childhood where he was not drunk.

15:39.554 --> 15:44.460
Thankfully, years later, he found healing and sobriety and ended up living a great and godly life.

15:44.480 --> 15:46.903
But during my childhood, I really kind of learned three things.

15:48.084 --> 15:50.107
I learned to keep the family secrets.

15:50.687 --> 15:53.110
I remembered at the age of five covered up.

15:54.172 --> 15:59.498
I learned to read the room what's going to happen.

16:00.459 --> 16:09.490
And I learned to strive and perform to try to keep everything stable.

16:10.306 --> 16:17.858
And so I spent years thinking that my identity, my worth was in what I do, what I produce, how I perform, how I achieve, how I deliver.

16:17.898 --> 16:22.225
That's how I keep everybody safe and stable.

16:23.848 --> 16:27.313
And those lies don't just necessarily disappear when you get saved.

16:28.194 --> 16:35.506
You're forgiven, you're spiritually reborn, but your soul, your mind, will, and emotion still takes time to heal.

16:39.394 --> 16:44.823
And many of you, you're stuck in someplace right now in the middle and you can relate.

16:46.366 --> 16:51.033
You're not falling apart, but you're also not living the life that God wants for you.

16:51.875 --> 16:53.437
And sometimes you're like the blind man.

16:55.340 --> 16:59.487
You're hurting and you're not strong enough to take the next step.

17:01.971 --> 17:05.938
It is in those moments you need some wing people.

17:08.354 --> 17:20.226
You need the body of Christ, and God uses ordinary people to help carry you when you can't carry yourself.

17:20.246 --> 17:26.412
And other times, you're not the blind man, but you're one of the unnamed people.

17:27.433 --> 17:28.274
You're some people.

17:29.495 --> 17:36.562
You notice when someone's hurting, and you care about the one that's struggling

17:37.122 --> 17:56.050
And when other people step back, you don't, you step in because you care and you love and you carry them and you carry their burdens and you may never get any credit and you may not even see the full miracle, but God uses people like you to start miracles that others could never begin on their own.

17:58.694 --> 18:07.026
And what I want you to see is it's we are designed by God to experience God with people in community.

18:07.810 --> 18:14.537
We best experience him with those together because he created us to know him and to love each other.

18:14.618 --> 18:23.127
And so if you're one of the ones right now that you're carrying someone, you're trying to bring someone to Jesus, you've got a spouse that needs hope and healing.

18:24.048 --> 18:31.076
You've got a child that's breaking your heart running from God and you're praying every day for help, protection, do whatever it takes.

18:31.096 --> 18:36.722
You've got a friend that you love, someone you're believing for, you're standing for,

18:36.834 --> 18:40.138
What I want to tell you right now takes us to the spiritual bank.

18:40.359 --> 18:48.209
Never underestimate what God can do when you simply bring someone to Jesus.

18:48.249 --> 18:53.577
You point them to Jesus, you pray them to Jesus, you invite them into his presence.

18:53.637 --> 19:01.267
And if you're like the blind man and you're hurting right now and you're struggling emotionally, here's what I want to say to you and I want you to hear this.

19:01.307 --> 19:06.354
I want to tell you as your pastor, if more than one person

19:06.946 --> 19:18.964
in your life that knows you and loves you and cares about you if more than one person like that tells you that you need help, you probably need help.

19:20.286 --> 19:22.850
And I wanna tell you, that is not an attack.

19:23.931 --> 19:26.615
That's actually love and kindness.

19:27.937 --> 19:32.905
And if right now you feel like God may be speaking to you, what I wanna tell you right now is He's speaking to you.

19:34.027 --> 19:36.370
You are not here by accident.

19:37.538 --> 19:38.999
You are not alone in the middle.

19:40.060 --> 19:40.701
God cares.

19:41.522 --> 19:41.982
I care.

19:42.743 --> 19:43.263
We care.

19:43.303 --> 19:45.826
The people around you care.

19:45.886 --> 19:48.228
And he's not going to leave you stuck in the middle.

19:49.970 --> 19:51.631
Jesus sees this guy.

19:52.732 --> 19:53.493
And he does something.

19:53.573 --> 19:54.534
No one asked him to do.

19:55.655 --> 19:57.197
And no one expected him to do.

19:57.857 --> 19:58.778
Scripture tells us this.

19:59.559 --> 20:02.021
He took the blind man by the hand.

20:02.542 --> 20:02.962
I like this.

20:03.663 --> 20:04.163
What did he do?

20:04.203 --> 20:07.186
The first thing he did is he touched the blind man

20:07.842 --> 20:08.543
by the hand.

20:09.625 --> 20:14.312
He reached out and grabbed him by the hand and let him outside the village.

20:15.273 --> 20:24.547
When he'd spit on the man's eyes, which is admittedly odd, if I pray for you today, I will not spit on your eyes.

20:26.370 --> 20:32.539
I'll just pray because I'm not Jesus and he can do that, but I'm not going to try.

20:33.981 --> 20:37.426
When he spit on the man's eyes and put his hands on him,

20:37.730 --> 20:40.893
Jesus asked him, do you see anything?

20:40.933 --> 20:45.097
He looked up and said, I see people.

20:46.038 --> 20:49.441
They look like trees walking around.

20:49.461 --> 20:54.265
I see something, but it's not completely clear.

20:55.306 --> 20:56.227
I love the imagery.

20:56.247 --> 21:04.955
The first thing Jesus does is he takes the man by the hand and walks with him because healing is often a journey with Jesus.

21:05.936 --> 21:07.698
And then he asks a guy, do you see anything?

21:08.098 --> 21:10.821
And he's like, I see people, they look like trees.

21:10.921 --> 21:13.864
I mean, imagine what it's like to see for the first time.

21:14.705 --> 21:17.869
My youngest son, Stephen, he's really, really smart.

21:18.390 --> 21:19.331
And he was struggling reading.

21:19.631 --> 21:20.832
We thought, what's wrong with this kid?

21:21.533 --> 21:22.714
We didn't ever think.

21:23.095 --> 21:24.476
Maybe his eyes were bad.

21:24.997 --> 21:25.838
We took him to the doctor.

21:25.878 --> 21:26.699
They tested his eyes.

21:26.719 --> 21:27.760
They put these glasses on him.

21:27.780 --> 21:32.365
And I remember the first time he saw great, because he got so big.

21:32.445 --> 21:36.530
